title: Cupid Always Wins (1951) A masterclass in 'No' — until LOVE calls her bluff.

sources.title: Cupid Always Wins (1951) A masterclass in 'No' — until LOVE calls her bluff.
sources.description:
A magazine photographer, Bill, flips the script on Dorinda Hatch, the sharp-tongued author of an anti-romance book against men.

The Lady Says No is a 1951 American romantic comedy film directed by Frank Ross, and written by Robert Russell.

Main actors:
Joan Caulfield - Dorinda Hatch
David Niven - Bill Shelby
James Robertson Justice - Matthew Hatch
Lenore Lonergan - Goldie
Frances Bavier - Aunt Alice Hatch
Peggy Maley - Midge
Henry Jones - Potsy
Jeff York - Goose
George Davis - Warf Rat Bartender
Robert Williams - General Schofield
Mary Lawrence - Mary


Black & White version: https://youtu.be/qkycyFWy80E
